at0029.1.description: The type of specimen to be collected e.g venous blood, prostatic biopsy.

at0007.1.description: The method of collection to be used eg Venepuncture, biopsy. resection.

at0005.1.description: Any risk or biohazard associated with  collecting or handling the specimen.

at0025.1.description: Any special preservative or transport medium requirements.

at0085.1.description: Any conditions associated with handling the specimen in-transit e.g 'Keep refrigerated'.

at0090.1.description: The date and time after which the specimen can no longer be used for testing.

at0042.1.description: Specific issue with a received specimen.

at0041.1.description: Is the specimen adequate for testing?
